=A0</em>that he was joking the stock tanked and Farnsworth got mad. Prosecu=
tors and the SEC argue that they=C2=A0<em>weren=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>kidding=
, that they were trying to deceive investors, and that it worked and invest=
ors were deceived. From the SEC:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In November 2017, HMNY issued $100=
 million in convertible notes and, in January 2018, an additional $60 milli=
on in convertible notes. In February 2018, HMNY also conducted a public off=
ering of warrants, which raised approximately $97 million. These HMNY secur=
ities offerings coincided with Farnsworth=E2=80=99s and Lowe=E2=80=99s mate=
rially false and misleading public statements regarding MoviePass, and HMNY=
 used the proceeds of the offerings to finance its investments in both HMNY=
 and MoviePass.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But Helios &amp; Matheson=E2=80=99s=C2=A0marke=
t capitalization peaked at about $300 million in October 2017; by summer 20=
