5px;">FTX vs. Binance</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you were a salesperson at a big investment =
bank in August 2008, it might have been a good idea to call up some hedge f=
unds and say =E2=80=9Chey, we are hearing some bad things about Lehman Brot=
hers. Do you feel safe with them? Might be a good time to move your account=
s over here.=E2=80=9D The hedge funds might have believed you =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0you would have been correct! =E2=80=94=C2=A0and moved their accounts to =
your bank. You would have done more business and made more money. At the en=
d of the year, you could go to your boss and say =E2=80=9CI won all these a=
ccounts from Lehman, give me a big bonus.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then your boss, if she was smart, would ha=
ve fired you.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you were the chief executive officer of a b=
ig investment bank in August 2008, and your subordinates were doing that so=
rt of thing, how would you have felt about it? Three possibilities are:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Good: They were being aggressive abou=
t winning business, and winning more business is good.</li>=09<li style=3D"=
margin-bottom: 5px;">Bad: Investment banking is a genteel business, and bad=
mouthing a competitor is rude.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Ver=
y bad: The banking system was in perilous shape, and doing anything to unde=
rmine confidence in the system =E2=80=94=C2=A0like, for instance, spreading=
 rumors that a competitor was collapsing =E2=80=94=C2=A0would have negative=
 effects on=C2=A0<em>your=C2=A0</em>bank. If Lehman failed, or even looked =
likely to fail, you might be next. Better to prop up confidence in your com=
petitors than to tear them down. Not all the time! In good times, sure, com=
pete fiercely. But in a crisis, be extremely polite.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think actual attitudes in 2008 were a mix of=
 all three, but among smart investment bank CEOs the third attitude was=C2=
=A0<em>very </em>prominent.=C2=A0In 2008, the job of an investment bank was=
 not to win market share; it was to stay alive. And staying alive was not a=
 zero-sum game; each bank was more likely to stay alive if its competitors =
did. The way to stay alive was not by convincing everyone that you were bet=
ter than the competition. The way to stay alive was by convincing everyone =
that=C2=A0<em>everything=C2=A0</em>was fine, that the system was fine. Bad =
news for one bank was bad news for everyone.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The crypto industry right now is interesting i=
n that:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It has recently suffered a crisis in c=
onfidence, with falling asset prices, contagion, rapid deleveraging and ban=
kruptcies of prominent firms.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Some=
 prominent firms turned out to be scams and Ponzis, and it=E2=80=99s reason=
able to assume that there will be more.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: =
5px;">There seems to be a very wide range of risk management practices, com=
pliance, etc., and some prominent firms are probably=C2=A0<em>much=C2=A0</e=
m>safer than others.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think this poses a challenge if you are the =
CEO of a big crypto firm. Unlike the big bank CEOs in 2008, you are probabl=
y on Twitter a lot. If there are negative rumors about a big competitor, do=
 you take to Twitter to say =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=99re not a scam like those gu=
ys=E2=80=9D? One advantage of doing that is that=C2=A0you might win some bu=
siness and harm a competitor; crypto is a smaller business than it was a ye=
ar ago, so winning market share is very valuable. Another advantage is that=
=C2=A0you don=E2=80=99t want people thinking that <em>you=E2=80=99re </em>a=
 scam; saying =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=99re not a scam like those guys=E2=80=9D is=
 one way to persuade people that you aren=E2=80=99t.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The disadvantage is that it is probably in you=
r long-term interest for people to be confident that=C2=A0<em>none=C2=A0</e=
m>of the big crypto businesses are scams. =E2=80=9CCrypto is full of scams =
and you can=E2=80=99t trust even the biggest exchanges=E2=80=9D is a=C2=A0<=
em>bad message for a crypto exchange to send</em>; adding =E2=80=9Cexcept u=
s, you can trust us=E2=80=9D=C2=A0<em>does not help.</em></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also I suppose you might consider the truth or=
 falsity of these rumors =E2=80=94=C2=A0maybe you should tweet =E2=80=9Cwe=
=E2=80=99re not a scam like those guys=E2=80=9D if those guys=C2=A0<em>are =
</em>a scam, or tweet =E2=80=9Cno those guys are fine=E2=80=9D if they aren=
=E2=80=99t=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0but I=E2=80=99m not sure that=E2=80=99s the =
most important factor.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/29619421.264507/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMDcvYmFua21hbi1mcmllZC1jei16aGFvLXRlbnNpb25zLXNwaWxsLWludG8=
