on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Anyway</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Simmering tensions between the crypto industry=
=E2=80=99s two richest executives are spilling over into the already batter=
ed digital-asset market.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On Sunday, Zhao =E2=80=9CCZ=E2=80=9D Changpeng=
, the billionaire chief executive of Binance Holdings Ltd. took to Twitter =
to announce plans to sell Binance=E2=80=99s roughly $530 million holding of=
 FTT, the native token of Sam Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s FTX. Binance and FTX =
run the world=E2=80=99s largest and seventh-largest crypto exchanges.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Zhao said his decision was triggered by =E2=80=
=9Crecent revelations.=E2=80=9D In a Nov. 2 article, news site CoinDesk sai=
d much of the balance sheet of Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s trading house Alamed=
a Research is comprised of the FTT token. FTT=E2=80=99s price fell in high =
trading volumes after Zhao=E2=80=99s announcement and traders rushed to wit=
hdraw funds from FTX.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Caroline Ellison, CEO of Alameda, responded on=
 Sunday to the CoinDesk story by saying =E2=80=9Cthat specific balance shee=
t is for a subset of our corporate entities, we have &gt;$10b of assets tha=
t aren=E2=80=99t reflected here.=E2=80=9D Ellison later offered to buy all =
the FTT tokens from Binance at a price of $22. The coin was trading just ab=
ove that level on Monday.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Prices of most cryptocurrencies fell on Monday=
, even as equities advanced.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bryce Elder <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/29619421.264507/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQv=
MWQxZmJkNTEtNzA4OS00MzkyLThlZjMtY2EzMDM1NzExNmFjP3NoYXJlVHlwZT1ub25naWZ0/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB99d8e32d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> writes</a> that =E2=80=9Cthough C=
Z insisted that his actions were not =E2=80=98a move against a competitor,=
=E2=80=99 it=E2=80=99s worth noting there is little love lost between him a=
nd SBF,=E2=80=9D and that=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cjust a few days ago, SBF was making=
 rather pointed allusions to CZ=E2=80=99s probity,=E2=80=9D but that =E2=80=
=9CSBF=E2=80=99s reaction to the latest development has (so far) been somew=
hat less adversarial.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0Roughly speaking, CZ seems to think tha=
t bad news for FTX is good news for Binance, while SBF =E2=80=94=C2=A0who h=
as spent a lot of this year=E2=80=99s crypto winter <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29619421.264507/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnVzaW5lc=
3NpbnNpZGVyLmNvbS9zYW0tYmFua21hbi1mcmllZC1mdHgtd2h5LWJhaWxpbmctY3J5cHRvLWNv=
bXBhbmllcy1tYXJrZXQtcm91dC0yMDIyLTc/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb766e9a5" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;"> bailing out</a>=C2=A0failed crypto companies =E2=80=94=C2=A0seems to t=
hink that bad news for one crypto firm is bad news for all of them. You wan=
t to win market share, but mostly you want crypto prices to go up.</p>
